---
title: Butternut Squash-Filled Pasta in a Garlic Cream Sauce with Roasted Bell Pepper
description: Tender pasta pillows are good in any form, but they’re *especially* good when packed with sweet butternut squash purée. Add tender strips of roasted bell pepper and a cheesy garlic cream sauce to the mix and you’ve got yourself a winning dinner. Luckily, this elegant pasta is as easy to make as it is delicious. All you need is 35 minutes for this dish to hit your table.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/garlic-cream-butternut-squash-agnolotti-9fe9d57c.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/garlic-cream-butternut-squash-agnolotti-5d8124c30d2e1146fd11b672-842bd3d1.pdf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
servings: 2
course: main course
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 700 kcal
  fat: 38 g
  saturated fat: 18 g
  carbohydrates: 57 g
  sugar: 17 g
  protein: 19 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 960 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/garlic-cream-butternut-squash-agnolotti-5d8124c30d2e1146fd11b672
time required: 35 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 400 degrees. Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Halve @bell pepper{1}; remove stem and seeds. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Drizzle bell pepper halves with @olive oil{3%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}; arrange cut sides down on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Place @garlic{2%cloves} in the center of a small piece of #foil{}; drizzle with oil and season with salt and pepper. Cinch into a packet and place on same sheet. Roast until bell pepper is lightly charred and garlic is softened, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Once bell pepper and garlic have roasted ~{15%minutes}, add @butternut squash pasta{9%ounce} to #pot{} of boiling water; reduce to a low simmer. Cook until al dente and floating to the top, ~{3-5%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water (1 cup for 4 servings), then drain and set aside.

Once done, transfer roasted bell pepper halves and garlic cloves to a #cutting board{}. Thinly slice bell pepper and gently mash garlic with a #fork{} until smooth.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in pot used for pasta over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Add ¼ cup reserved pasta cooking water (⅓ cup for 4), @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @cream cheese{2%tablespoon}, @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, half the @parmesan cheese{¼%cup}, and @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4); stir until smooth. Stir in sliced bell pepper and mashed garlic. Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat. Season with salt and pepper.

Stir pasta into sauce. If needed, add more reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is fully coated. Divide between #bowls{}. Season with pepper. Garnish with scallion greens and remaining Parmesan.